description: A missed connection is when two people briefly cross paths, feel a possible connection, but don’t get the chance to talk further or exchange contact information.  I once had a brief interaction with a girl. We smiled at each other. I saw her again on a beach, but I wasn’t confident enough to approach her. I didn’t know her name, who her friends were, or where she studied. It was a huge city, and I knew the chances of ever seeing her again were slim unless destiny had something planned. But I wasn’t that lucky. I never saw her again.  Even now, that moment stays with me. I often wonder how two strangers who felt something could they ever find each other again. If they don’t know names, addresses, or any personal details. That question stayed with me and eventually sparked the idea for this project.  YouLookedAt.me is a platform where you can share your missed connection moment. If someone else posts a story that matches yours, you’ll be notified and can start a chat.
